HB 485 Original 2026 Regular Session Amedee
Abstract: Adds the fundamental right of parents to decide the nurturing, education, care,
custody, and control of their children.
Proposed constitutional amendment adds the fundamental right of parents to decide the
nurturing, education, care, custody, and control of their children.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that any denial, infringement, or restriction of
this right is subject to strict scrutiny unless there is a higher level of protection or scrutiny
recognized and applied by the court.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held Nov. 3, 2026.
(Adds Const. Art. I, §28)
